                  MARY 
                  MILLER
               <interp inst="t18280911-296-person1640" type="surname" value="MILLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-296-person1640" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-296-person1640" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Frederick Miller, and live at Somer's-town. On the afternoon of the 16th of August, I went out to get some flour; the prisoner came into the shop where I was, and from there he crossed and went into mine - I saw him goacross my shop, and into the parlour where I had left my watch; I did not see him take it, but crossed directly - I missed it, and detained him; I accused him of having been into my room - he denied it, but I found the watch in his bosom.</p>
